WEBVTT

01:05.282 --> 01:07.545
- Why are you smiling?

01:07.632 --> 01:10.113
- Because it's the most
wonderful time of the year.

01:10.200 --> 01:13.638
The smell of fresh pine,
cocoa, cinnamon.

01:13.725 --> 01:15.205
You are so lucky.

01:15.292 --> 01:17.338
I mean, I can't wait
to have all of this.

01:17.425 --> 01:18.513
- Wait, kids?

01:21.951 --> 01:23.518
You can have 'em.

01:23.605 --> 01:24.910
- I should probably find
my Prince Charming first.

01:24.997 --> 01:26.782
- Please, just take my kids.

01:26.869 --> 01:29.654
- Mom!
- Behave.
I will leave you with Santa.

01:29.741 --> 01:33.136
- Yay!

01:33.223 --> 01:34.920
- Oh, how was the speed-dating
event I set you up on?

01:35.007 --> 01:36.183
Any keepers?
- It was...

01:36.270 --> 01:37.358
- Juicy?

01:37.445 --> 01:38.620
- Uh...
- It was scandalous?

01:38.707 --> 01:40.535
- Non-existent.
- What?

01:40.622 --> 01:42.014
- Next.

01:42.102 --> 01:44.539
-
Holly, you are in your prime.

01:44.626 --> 01:47.194
You should have a line of guys
waiting to take you out.

01:48.673 --> 01:50.414
Can you put the phone down?

01:50.501 --> 01:52.199
- I'm following up
- with the Bell/
- Boyer account.

01:52.286 --> 01:53.504
Their marketing team
wants to do that shoot

01:53.591 --> 01:55.289
before Christmas.

01:55.376 --> 01:57.421
- Okay, fine, but once
you nail down the shoot,

01:57.508 --> 01:58.814
can you put it away?

01:58.901 --> 02:01.077
- Yes.
- Gotta keep perspective, babe.

02:01.164 --> 02:03.732
We run an ad agency,
not air traffic control.

02:05.777 --> 02:07.344
Look, Holly, I love you, I do,

02:07.431 --> 02:10.913
but this whole workaholic
thing, it's not healthy.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.915
When's the last time
you a trimmed a tree?

02:13.002 --> 02:16.005
Isn't this supposed to be
the most wonderful time
of the year?

02:16.092 --> 02:17.659
- Does the one on my desk count?

02:18.703 --> 02:20.923
- <i>Courtney,
please come to office 105.</i>

02:21.010 --> 02:22.794
<i>We have another paper jam.</i>

02:22.881 --> 02:24.492
- Holly.

02:24.579 --> 02:26.015
- Look, there will be plenty
of time for tree-trimming

02:26.102 --> 02:28.278
and all that other stuff later.

02:28.365 --> 02:30.237
- Life does not start later.

02:30.324 --> 02:32.717
The holidays do not start later.

02:32.804 --> 02:34.241
Here, take my card.

02:34.328 --> 02:36.025
I want you to go
to the tree farm,

02:36.112 --> 02:38.419
and I want you to buy the most
beautiful one you can find.

02:38.506 --> 02:40.464
- But--
- No buts.

02:40.551 --> 02:42.510
Consider this a direct
order from your boss.

02:42.597 --> 02:43.946
And I will be checking
the charges

02:44.033 --> 02:45.339
to make sure you follow through.

02:45.426 --> 02:47.558
- Fine, I will go buy a tree.

02:47.645 --> 02:49.038
- Now, if we can
find you somebody

02:49.125 --> 02:51.606
to share this beautifully
trimmed tree with...

02:51.693 --> 02:53.129
- Yeah,

02:53.216 --> 02:55.653
I think all the guys
in this line are taken.

02:55.740 --> 02:57.786
- Everyone gets a wish
on Christmas.

03:01.006 --> 03:02.269
- I guess there's hope yet.

03:02.356 --> 03:03.705
- What do you mean?

03:03.792 --> 03:05.794
- Well, I could always use
my Christmas wish

03:05.881 --> 03:07.796
to find my happily ever after.

03:07.883 --> 03:08.971
- Well, better late than never.

03:09.058 --> 03:10.712
- Okay, all right.

03:10.799 --> 03:13.062
My Christmas wish
is to meet Mr. Right.

03:13.149 --> 03:14.672
-
- Stop beating up your sister.

03:14.759 --> 03:17.066
I will ground you for life.

03:17.153 --> 03:19.068
I'm sorry.
What was that last part?

03:19.155 --> 03:22.680
- I said, my Christmas wish
is to meet Mr. Right.

03:22.767 --> 03:24.247
- Hey, she got two wishes.

03:24.334 --> 03:25.422
- No,
she didn't mean it, sweetie.

03:25.509 --> 03:26.945
She's just very lonely.

03:27.032 --> 03:28.251
- Next.

03:30.166 --> 03:32.255
- All right, slow down.

03:32.342 --> 03:34.126
- Merry Christmas
-

05:43.734 --> 05:44.996
- Hmm.

05:45.083 --> 05:46.781
Nope.

05:49.392 --> 05:51.742
That's a little bit too big.

05:52.743 --> 05:54.528
Hm. Nope.

05:57.095 --> 05:59.446
Oh, you're cute.

06:03.363 --> 06:04.538
Hmm.

06:09.020 --> 06:10.152
Come here.

06:22.860 --> 06:24.384
Help.

06:27.952 --> 06:29.345
- Miss, are you okay?

06:29.432 --> 06:31.391
- Yeah, I'm fine.
I don't know what happened.

06:31.478 --> 06:34.524
- I do. I think that tree
fell over on you.

06:34.611 --> 06:36.831
Let me help you up.
I'm Tom Wright.

06:38.267 --> 06:39.877
- Oh.

06:39.964 --> 06:41.531
Mr. Wright?

06:41.618 --> 06:43.707
- Oh, please,
you can just call me Tom.

06:46.231 --> 06:48.146
So can I help you find a tree?

06:48.233 --> 06:50.279
- Actually,
I think the tree picked me.

06:50.366 --> 06:52.586
- Well, you can't go wrong
with a classic noble fir,

06:52.673 --> 06:56.590
but would you consider maybe
a Colorado blue spruce?

06:56.677 --> 06:58.592
They are super
on trend this year.

06:58.679 --> 07:01.246
- I think I'm gonna go
with the noble fir.

07:02.857 --> 07:05.337
You sure know a lot about trees.
Do you work here?

07:05.425 --> 07:08.819
- No. No, I don't work here,
but I love Christmas.

07:08.906 --> 07:11.213
And I'm actually here picking
out a tree for myself.

07:11.300 --> 07:13.607
- Can I help you with that?
- Nah, I got it, pal.

07:13.694 --> 07:15.130
- Okay.

07:15.217 --> 07:19.395
- So, um, I guess that's it.
Noble fir it is.

07:19.482 --> 07:20.918
- That's the one.

07:21.005 --> 07:21.963
- Let me help you with that.

07:22.050 --> 07:23.094
- All right.

07:26.924 --> 07:28.665
- Come on, let's go.

07:30.014 --> 07:31.973
That should do it.

07:32.060 --> 07:33.540
Proper knot for a proper tree.

07:36.107 --> 07:38.414
You know, I never got your name.

07:38.501 --> 07:41.199
- Oh, I'm Holly.
Nice to meet you.

07:41.286 --> 07:43.854
- Well, nice meetin' you,
Holly.

07:43.941 --> 07:46.814
You're all set,
so happy holidays.

07:46.901 --> 07:48.337
- You too, and thank you.

07:48.424 --> 07:50.426
- Sure, don't mention it.

07:50.513 --> 07:51.471
Take care.

07:52.646 --> 07:54.082
- Wow.

07:54.169 --> 07:55.387
- You know, Holly.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.085
- Yeah?

07:58.869 --> 08:02.612
- Would you like to, um, um...

08:02.699 --> 08:04.962
get some dinner sometime?

08:05.049 --> 08:06.573
I mean, if I'm not overstepping.

08:06.660 --> 08:09.010
- I would love that.

08:09.097 --> 08:11.055
- Yeah?
- Give me your phone.

08:11.142 --> 08:13.580
- Okay, um.

08:13.667 --> 08:14.885
Here you go.

08:23.024 --> 08:25.983
Okay, well, I'm a walkin'
away for real this time.

08:27.855 --> 08:29.509
- Okay.

08:29.596 --> 08:31.902
- But I'll call you,
because I can now,

08:31.989 --> 08:34.514
and we can go get that dinner
sometime if you want to.

08:34.601 --> 08:35.906
- Really lookin' forward to it.

08:35.993 --> 08:38.996
- Okay. Bye now.

08:39.083 --> 08:40.520
Bye.

09:20.777 --> 09:22.257
- Help!

09:22.344 --> 09:23.737
Help, a little help here!

09:23.824 --> 09:25.521
- Oh, my gosh, I'm so sorry.

09:29.525 --> 09:31.266
I'm so sorry. Here, let me help.

09:31.353 --> 09:32.441
Are you okay?
- Yeah.

09:32.528 --> 09:33.790
- I'm so sorry.

09:35.531 --> 09:36.619
Oh.

09:36.706 --> 09:38.273
- What happened?

09:38.360 --> 09:40.144
- I...
- It's okay. It's all right.

09:40.231 --> 09:41.972
I'm-- I'm all right. I'm fine.

09:42.059 --> 09:43.365
It's okay, really.

09:43.452 --> 09:45.193
Did you tie this thing up
onto your roof?

09:45.280 --> 09:47.412
- No, it was the guy
at the tree lot.

09:47.499 --> 09:49.980
I think he called it
a proper knot.

09:50.067 --> 09:51.155
- Proper knot?

09:51.242 --> 09:52.983
No, that doesn't even exist.

09:53.070 --> 09:55.072
Nah, this looks like a,
this looks like a slipknot.

09:55.159 --> 09:56.247
Should have done
like a timber hitch

09:56.334 --> 09:57.901
or maybe even a sheepshank,

09:57.988 --> 09:59.555
somethin' you can easily get
undone when you get home.

09:59.642 --> 10:01.818
I mean, what is this,
amateur hour here? I'm sorry.

10:01.905 --> 10:03.646
I don't mean to talk bad
about someone I haven't met.

10:03.733 --> 10:05.474
It's just, I mean, you really
could have hurt somebody.

10:05.561 --> 10:07.128
I'm sorry. What happened?

10:07.215 --> 10:08.695
Was he, like, havin' a bad day?

10:08.782 --> 10:10.653
Did he get distracted
or somethin'?

10:13.090 --> 10:14.265
Miss?

10:14.352 --> 10:16.311
- Yes. Yeah, absolutely.

10:17.617 --> 10:19.009
- Absolutely what?

10:20.837 --> 10:22.622
- To what you just said.

10:24.624 --> 10:26.147
- Right, um.

10:26.234 --> 10:28.018
Why don't I get this up
on your roof for you.

10:28.105 --> 10:29.933
- You know what, I just
live down the block.

10:30.020 --> 10:32.675
It's probably easier at this
point if I just carry it.

10:32.762 --> 10:35.460
- Oh. Okay, uh.

10:35.547 --> 10:37.071
Do you need a hand?

10:38.594 --> 10:39.813
- Sure.

10:39.900 --> 10:41.641
- Okay. Austin, by the way.

10:42.511 --> 10:43.555
- Holly.

10:43.643 --> 10:45.079
- Nice to meet you, Holly.

10:47.690 --> 10:50.432
- Lot of sap.

10:50.519 --> 10:52.521
I'll do it.

10:52.608 --> 10:54.131
Okay.
- Okay.

10:54.218 --> 10:55.611
- Pull up.

10:55.698 --> 10:56.917
All right, just,
yeah, get the...

10:57.004 --> 10:58.179
Once the trunk
is through there...

10:58.266 --> 10:59.049
- Yep.
- I can get it from there.

10:59.136 --> 11:00.050
Okay.
- Okay.

11:00.137 --> 11:01.312
- We're almost there.

11:01.399 --> 11:02.444
Okay.

11:05.229 --> 11:06.753
Okay.

11:06.840 --> 11:08.189
All right, we got it.
- Okay.

11:08.276 --> 11:09.886
- All right, goin' in here.

11:09.973 --> 11:11.279
- Yeah, just...
- Right here, whew.

11:11.366 --> 11:12.889
- That way.
Almost in the hole.

11:12.976 --> 11:14.543
Wait, no, a little to the left.

11:14.630 --> 11:16.240
To the right, the right. Okay!

11:16.327 --> 11:18.112
Right, right there, drop it.

11:18.199 --> 11:19.548
Okay.

11:22.769 --> 11:24.161
Oh.

11:26.511 --> 11:28.209
I meant get
something a little smaller.

11:30.211 --> 11:32.561
- It's fine,
just needs a little trimming.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.041
- Yeah, trimming.

11:35.390 --> 11:37.305
How do I do that?

11:37.392 --> 11:38.698
- You got some shears?

11:44.573 --> 11:46.227
- Yeah.

11:47.881 --> 11:49.839
- Okay, um.

11:49.926 --> 11:53.016
I think we're
gonna need somethin'
a little bigger than this.

11:53.103 --> 11:54.714
Do you, uh,
you got lights and decorations

11:54.801 --> 11:56.063
and all that kind of stuff?

12:00.284 --> 12:02.547
I think we're gonna need
to make a little trip.

12:02.634 --> 12:04.724
- Well, I've got this covered.

12:04.811 --> 12:06.726
- Okay, let's go.

12:08.553 --> 12:09.641
-
- What are those for?

12:09.729 --> 12:10.773
- Uh, tree trimming.

12:20.261 --> 12:21.349
- So cool.

12:23.133 --> 12:25.135
Both, why not.

12:25.222 --> 12:26.484
I did.

12:26.571 --> 12:28.008
Hummingbird?

12:32.142 --> 12:34.710
- That means
you have to make cookies.

12:34.797 --> 12:36.364
-
Against the green tree.
